{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566980","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566980"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18912"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18912","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18912"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.63,0.06,0.22,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11645"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80171"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11645","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11645"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18912"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65448"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11356"},{"type":"tags","id":"11357"},{"type":"tags","id":"11358"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27392"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27393"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80171","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80171"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is learning about providing culturally safe care. During a tutorial, various approaches to cross-cultural healthcare are discussed.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the practice of cultural safety in healthcare?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Treating all patients exactly the same way","Reflecting on own cultural beliefs while respecting patient perspectives","Delegating culturally diverse patients to staff of matching background","Learning facts about different cultural groups","Requiring patients to adapt to healthcare system norms"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach to cultural safety involves \u003Cstrong\u003Ereflecting on own cultural beliefs while respecting patient perspectives\u003C/strong\u003E. This practice requires healthcare providers to examine their own cultural assumptions, biases, and privileges while creating an environment where patients feel their cultural identity is respected and validated.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELearning facts about different cultural groups\u003C/strong\u003E - While cultural awareness is important, merely learning facts about cultures can lead to stereotyping and does not address power imbalances in healthcare\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreating all patients exactly the same way\u003C/strong\u003E - This approach ignores important cultural differences and may lead to inequitable care\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequiring patients to adapt to healthcare system norms\u003C/strong\u003E - This demonstrates cultural dominance and fails to respect patient autonomy and cultural identity\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelegating culturally diverse patients to staff of matching background\u003C/strong\u003E - This approach is discriminatory and assumes cultural matching is necessary for good care\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003ECultural safety emphasises the importance of healthcare providers understanding their own cultural positioning while working in partnership with patients to deliver care that respects and responds to cultural needs and preferences.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cultural safety requires healthcare providers to examine their own cultural beliefs and biases while respecting the patient\u0027s cultural identity.","Patient-centred care involves understanding and incorporating the patient\u0027s cultural perspectives into healthcare decisions.","Cultural safety goes beyond cultural awareness to create an environment where patients feel their cultural identity is respected and validated."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","So N, Price K, O\u0027Mara P, Rodrigues MA. The importance of cultural humility and cultural safety in health care. Med J Aust. 2024 Jan 15;220(1):12-13. doi: 10.5694/mja2.52182. Epub 2023 Dec 4. PMID: 38049948. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38049948/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65448"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18912"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65448","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65448"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-18T06:52:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T06:52:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11645"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80171"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Jun